    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stationary machines having a moving belt, disk, or spindle with an abrasive surface, usually a sandpaper; used for smoothing surfaces.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000027101/Smit, Means Illustrated Construction Dictionary (1985)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Vaste machines die een lopende band, schijf of spoel hebben met een schurend oppervlak, meestal van schuurpapier. Worden gebruikt om oppervlakken glad te maken.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
